definition.value: A 6-isopentenylaminopurine having a 3-amino-3-carboxypropyl group attached at the 3-position.

An organic heterobicyclic compound that consists of 2-oxohexahydro-1H-thieno[3,4-d]imidazole having a valeric acid substituent attached to the tetrahydrothiophene ring. The parent of the class of biotins.
A derivative of cyclohepta-1,3,5-triene having a carboxy group at position 1, an oxo group at position 5 and hydroxy groups at positions 3 and 6.
